# Unit 6 Lessons > Day 1

## Concepts Covered

What is a robot, criteria that make an item a robot.
 
## Lesson Overview

This unit starts by students brainstorming what they think of when they hear ”robot,” then they identify common features of robots.  There is also an extension activity to research Isaac Asimov’s Three Laws of Robotics.  This activity is similar to the what’s a computer activity in Unit 1.  It is a great way to connect back to that activity and talk about how the curriculum spirals, and take students on a journey of seeing how far they’ve come throughout the year.

